The causes of '''homelessness in Iraq''' are diverse. Forced evictions of [[internally displaced person]]s from public land and buildings have contributed heavily to the homeless population of the country.<ref name="Sabah">{{Cite book|title=Iraq and the Region|author=Sabah Arar|publisher=[[United Nations Children's Fund]]|page=35|url=http://ochadms.unog.ch/quickplace/cap/main.nsf/h_Index/CAP_2009_Iraq/$FILE/CAP_2009_Iraq_VOL1_SCREEN.pdf?OpenElement}}</ref>  In 2007, the [[United Nations]] estimated that 16% of the Iraqi population have fled their homes because of the [[Iraq War|conflict]], and half of these have left the country, leaving some of the remaining in the country homeless, though some rent housing or stay with family and friends.<ref name="Shirouk2007">{{Cite journal|title=Homeless in Iraq|journal=[[guardian.co.uk]]|author=Shirouk Alabayachi|author2=Robert Lowe|date=2007-10-27|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2007/oct/27/homelessiniraq}}</ref>

