{{Infobox organization |name = LeadNow |formation = 2010 |type = [[Non-profit]] |purpose = Healthy environment, [[just society]], fair economy, and open democracy |key_people = Lyndsay Poaps (Executive Director) |website = https://www.leadnow.ca }}
'''LeadNow''' (French: {{lang|fr|A L'action}}) is a Canadian [[non-profit]], multi-partisan citizens' advocacy organization formed in 2010.<ref name=About>{{cite web |url=https://www.leadnow.ca/faq/ |title=About LeadNow |publisher=LeadNow |date=2017 |accessdate=July 18, 2018}}</ref> It campaigns for changes to environmental policy, workers rights, education, and [[proportional representation]].<ref name=Campaigns>{{cite web |url=https://www.leadnow.ca/campaigns/ |title=Campaigns |publisher=LeadNow |date=2017 |accessdate=July 18, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://vancouversun.com/business/local-business/controversial-leadnow-active-in-b-c-politics-vancouver-city-affairs |title=Controversial Leadnow active in B.C. politics, Vancouver city affairs |last1=Shaw|first1=Rob |first2=Joanne |last2=Lee-Young |work=[[Vancouver Sun]]|date=May 23, 2017 |accessdate=July 18, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/ontario-sex-ed-plans-1.4742523 |title=Ontario going back to old sex-ed curriculum in fall, PCs say |last=[[The Canadian Press]] |work=[[CBC News]]|date=July 11, 2018 |accessdate=July 18, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://vancouversun.com/news/politics/yes-and-no-groups-selected-before-referendum-on-electoral-reform-in-b-c |title='Yes' side in electoral referendum has early advantage on spending |last=Shaw|first=Rob |work=[[Vancouver Sun]]|date=July 12, 2018 |accessdate=July 18, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=LeadNow |date=February 2018 |title=How We Vote - Leadnow's recommendations for the 2018 BC referendum on electoral reform. |url=https://engage.gov.bc.ca/app/uploads/sites/271/2018/02/Leadnow.pdf |work=LeadNow |access-date=July 19, 2018}}</ref>
The organization has been a vocal opponent to the [[Trans Mountain Pipeline]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news1130.com/2018/06/04/rallies-planned-canada-kinder-morgan-buyout/ | title=Rallies planned across Canada to protest Kinder Morgan buyout |date=June 4, 2018|accessdate=July 18, 2018 |last=[[The Canadian Press]] |work=[[News 1130]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/4138733/justin-trudeau-to-pressure-b-c-government-to-accept-trans-mountain-pipeline/ | title=Justin Trudeau to pressure B.C. government to accept Trans Mountain pipeline |date=April 11, 2018|accessdate=July 18, 2018 |work=[[Global News]] |last1=Ljunggren |first1=David |last2=Gordon |first2=Julie}}</ref>
During elections, LeadNow has advocated for its members to [[Tactical voting|vote strategically]] as a tool to advance its advocacy.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://thetyee.ca/News/2015/08/11/Leadnow-Strategic-Voting/ |title=How Leadnow Will Push Strategic Voting to Defeat Tories |last=Ward |first=Doug |work=[[The Tyee]]|date=August 11, 2015 |accessdate=July 18, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.straight.com/news/557836/leadnow-recommends-ndps-mira-oreck-vancouver-granville-despite-liberals-higher-polling |title=Leadnow recommends NDP's Mira Oreck in Vancouver Granville despite Liberal's higher polling result |last=Smith |first=Charlie |work=[[The Georgia Straight]]|date=October 15, 2015 |accessdate=July 19, 2018 }}</ref> ''Vote Together'' campaigns have targeted [[Swing (politics)|swing ridings]]. LeadNow's strategic voting efforts have been criticized by [[Canadian Union of Public Employees|CUPE]], the [[New Democratic Party]], [[Elizabeth May]] and others.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2015/04/13/cupe-leadnow-federal-election_n_7058128.html |title=CUPE Slams Leadnow For Encouraging Canadians To 'Vote Together' |last=Raj |first=Althia |work=[[Huffington Post]]|date=April 14, 2015 |accessdate=July 19, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://nationalpost.com/news/politics/armed-with-a-450000-member-mailing-list-group-mobilizes-against-tories-in-swing-ridings |title=Well-funded and armed with a 450,000-member mailing list, group targets Tories in swing ridings |last=[[Postmedia News]] |publisher=[[National Post]]|date=September 9, 2015 |accessdate=July 19, 2018 }}</ref>
